# Netlify _redirects — copied verbatim into dist/ by Vite.
#
# WHY THIS FILE EXISTS
# The npm `pyodide` package ships only the core runtime (pyodide.js,
# pyodide.asm.wasm, python_stdlib.zip, pyodide-lock.json). It does NOT
# ship the package wheels (micropip, packaging, numpy, pandas, ...).
# Pyodide expects to fetch those at runtime. When `indexURL` is set to a
# self-hosted path like /pyodide/, the wheels 404 because we never
# deployed them. The rule below redirects every wheel request to the
# canonical jsdelivr CDN — SRI integrity checks pass because the bytes
# match what pyodide-lock.json declares.
#
# Bump the version segment whenever you upgrade the pyodide npm package.

/pyodide/*.whl   https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/pyodide/v0.26.4/full/:splat   301!

# SPA fallback for the agent UI. Keep this LAST — it must not shadow the
# wheel rule above. Static assets under /pyodide/ that DO exist locally
# (pyodide.js, .wasm, .zip, pyodide-lock.json) are served directly by
# Netlify before reaching this rule.
/*   /index.html   200
